pick at IVF clinics,

00:47:15.010 --> 00:47:17.890
has a lot more to
do with control--

00:47:17.890 --> 00:47:19.910
one can always argue about that.

00:47:19.910 --> 00:47:21.490
And then you take this also--

00:47:21.490 --> 00:47:22.930
you tie it to what
we already see

00:47:22.930 --> 00:47:25.810
happening across
Asia in terms of sex

00:47:25.810 --> 00:47:30.340
discrimination, abortion, which
is warping the population.

00:47:30.340 --> 00:47:34.010
We already have experience
that this has done poorly.

00:47:34.010 --> 00:47:36.880
And so one of my
concerns, as you

00:47:36.880 --> 00:47:39.200
go in the world
working on this, is

00:47:39.200 --> 00:47:40.450
that there are actually women.

00:47:40.450 --> 00:47:43.750
And there's work going
the reproduction side.

00:47:43.750 --> 00:47:45.553
You said, toss IVF off.

00:47:45.553 --> 00:47:46.470
Oh, yes, this is here.

00:47:46.470 --> 00:47:47.530
It's standardized.

00:47:47.530 --> 00:47:50.550
And we have a lot more multiple
births, which are hugely--

00:47:50.550 --> 00:47:51.280
JAMIE METZL: Well,
that's going down.

00:47:51.280 --> 00:47:51.680
Yeah.

00:47:51.680 --> 00:47:52.263
AUDIENCE: Yes.

00:47:52.263 --> 00:47:55.930
But they're riskier-- the chance
of it, the medicalization.

00:47:55.930 --> 00:47:57.940
This all has huge implications.

00:47:57.940 --> 00:48:00.220
We talk about, oh,
wouldn't it be lovely

00:48:00.220 --> 00:48:01.990
if your kids are smarter?

00:48:01.990 --> 00:48:03.610
I have three smart kids.

00:48:03.610 --> 00:48:05.260
And asynchronous
development-- there's

00:48:05.260 --> 00:48:08.770
all of these societal
implications that are embedded

00:48:08.770 --> 00:48:10.120
in the culture assumptions.

00:48:10.120 --> 00:48:11.150
Oh, this must be great.

00:48:11.150 --> 00:48:14.740
But getting there is
hugely challenging.

00:48:14.740 --> 00:48:16.390
JAMIE METZL: I totally
agree that there

00:48:16.390 --> 00:48:20.020
are huge issues of women's
health, reproductive health.

00:48:20.020 --> 00:48:24.730
And we are moving into
a new world of biology

00:48:24.730 --> 00:48:26.500
and how biology works.

00:48:26.500 --> 00:48:29.710
So I've talked about
how egg cells will

00:48:29.710 --> 00:48:32.830
be created from adult cells.

00:48:32.830 --> 00:48:35.390
We already have--
in the last year,

00:48:35.390 --> 00:48:40.570
two male mice have had their own
100% related biological child.

00:48:40.570 --> 00:48:44.260
Two female mice have
had their own 100%

00:48:44.260 --> 00:48:46.390
related biological child.

00:48:46.390 --> 00:48:50.160
We are moving into a
world where biology

00:48:50.160 --> 00:48:54.870
is fundamentally different
than what we have known.

00:48:54.870 --> 00:49:00.030
And the possibilities that that
will bring are, in many ways,

00:49:00.030 --> 00:49:02.200
beyond most of our imagination.

00:49:02.200 --> 00:49:03.090
Thank you so much.

00:49:03.090 --> 00:49:05.640
It's really been a
pleasure speaking with you.

00:49:05.640 --> 00:49:09.590
